  "text": "In order to protect cell monolayers from virus infection by using MAbs, it is convenient to use an antibody that has a high titer for virus neutralization, that recognizes an epitope present in all virus isolates, and that does not lead to the selection of neutralization escape mutants. These conditions were fulfilled by MAb 6A.C3 (17, [CITATION_1] .",
